# XMX Matrix Optimization Prompt for BMG B60
# Target: Intel BMG B60 GPU (Xe2 Architecture, Device 0xe211)
# Goal: Achieve 100+ TFLOPS using XMX (Xe Matrix Extensions)

## Context

You are optimizing a SYCL kernel for Intel BMG B60 GPU using XMX hardware acceleration.

**Hardware Specs:**
- Architecture: Xe2 (Battlemage)
- Compute Units: 160 EUs
- XMX Peak: 320 TFLOPS (FP16)
- Tile Size: 8×16×16 (M×N×K)
- Required Subgroup: 16 lanes
- SLM: 256 KB per work-group

## Optimization Checklist

### Phase 1: Compilation Setup
- [ ] Use AOT compilation for BMG: `-fsycl-targets=spir64_gen -Xsycl-target-backend "-device bmg"`
- [ ] Enable large GRF mode: `-options -ze-opt-large-register-file`
- [ ] Include XMX header: `#include <sycl/ext/oneapi/matrix/matrix.hpp>`
- [ ] Use namespace: `using namespace sycl::ext::oneapi::experimental::matrix;`

### Phase 2: Kernel Configuration
- [ ] Set tile constants: `constexpr int TM=8, TN=16, TK=16;`
- [ ] Add subgroup attribute: `[[sycl::reqd_sub_group_size(16)]]`
- [ ] Configure work-group: `sycl::range<2> local(8, 16);`
- [ ] Cast pointers to multi_ptr using `address_space_cast`

### Phase 3: XMX Implementation
- [ ] Declare joint_matrix tiles: `sub_a` (use::a), `sub_b` (use::b), `sub_c` (use::accumulator)
- [ ] Initialize with `joint_matrix_fill(sg, sub_c, 0.0f)`
- [ ] Loop over K with `#pragma unroll 4`
- [ ] Load tiles with `joint_matrix_load`
- [ ] Compute with `joint_matrix_mad` (DPAS instruction)
- [ ] Store with `joint_matrix_store`

### Phase 4: Testing & Validation
- [ ] Test sizes: 2048, 4096, 8192, 16384
- [ ] Verify compilation: No errors, AOT for BMG
- [ ] Check performance: Target >100 TFLOPS at 4096×4096
- [ ] Calculate utilization: (TFLOPS / 320) × 100%

## Standard XMX Template

```cpp
#include <sycl/sycl.hpp>
#include <sycl/ext/oneapi/matrix/matrix.hpp>

using namespace sycl::ext::oneapi::experimental::matrix;

constexpr int TM = 8, TN = 16, TK = 16;

void kernel_xmx(sycl::half* C, const sycl::half* A, const sycl::half* B,
                int M, int N, int K, sycl::queue& q) {
    sycl::range<2> global((M + TM - 1) / TM, (N + TN - 1) / TN);
    sycl::range<2> local(8, 16);
    
    q.parallel_for(sycl::nd_range<2>(global, local),
        [=](sycl::nd_item<2> item) [[sycl::reqd_sub_group_size(16)]] {
        
        sycl::sub_group sg = item.get_sub_group();
        
        // Cast pointers
        auto pA = sycl::address_space_cast<
            sycl::access::address_space::global_space,
            sycl::access::decorated::no>(const_cast<sycl::half*>(A));
        auto pB = sycl::address_space_cast<
            sycl::access::address_space::global_space,
            sycl::access::decorated::no>(const_cast<sycl::half*>(B));
        auto pC = sycl::address_space_cast<
            sycl::access::address_space::global_space,
            sycl::access::decorated::no>(C);
        
        // Declare tiles
        joint_matrix<sycl::sub_group, sycl::half, use::a, TM, TK, layout::row_major> sub_a;
        joint_matrix<sycl::sub_group, sycl::half, use::b, TK, TN, layout::row_major> sub_b;
        joint_matrix<sycl::sub_group, sycl::half, use::accumulator, TM, TN> sub_c;
        
        // Initialize
        joint_matrix_fill(sg, sub_c, sycl::half(0.0f));
        
        // Compute
        #pragma unroll 4
        for (int k = 0; k < K / TK; k++) {
            joint_matrix_load(sg, sub_a, 
                pA + (item.get_global_id(0) * TM) * K + k * TK, K);
            joint_matrix_load(sg, sub_b, 
                pB + (k * TK) * N + item.get_global_id(1) * TN, N);
            joint_matrix_mad(sg, sub_c, sub_a, sub_b, sub_c);
        }
        
        // Store
        joint_matrix_store(sg, sub_c, 
            pC + (item.get_global_id(0) * TM) * N + item.get_global_id(1) * TN, 
            N, layout::row_major);
    });
    q.wait();
}
```

## Compilation Command

```bash
icpx -fsycl -O3 -std=c++17 \
  -fsycl-targets=spir64_gen \
  -Xsycl-target-backend "-device bmg -options -ze-opt-large-register-file" \
  -o kernel kernel.cpp
```

## Performance Harness

```cpp
void benchmark(int M, int N, int K, sycl::queue& q) {
    // Allocate
    sycl::half* d_A = sycl::malloc_device<sycl::half>(M * K, q);
    sycl::half* d_B = sycl::malloc_device<sycl::half>(K * N, q);
    sycl::half* d_C = sycl::malloc_device<sycl::half>(M * N, q);
    
    // Init
    std::vector<sycl::half> h_A(M * K, sycl::half(0.01f));
    std::vector<sycl::half> h_B(K * N, sycl::half(0.01f));
    q.memcpy(d_A, h_A.data(), M * K * sizeof(sycl::half)).wait();
    q.memcpy(d_B, h_B.data(), K * N * sizeof(sycl::half)).wait();
    
    // Warmup
    for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) kernel_xmx(d_C, d_A, d_B, M, N, K, q);
    q.wait();
    
    // Benchmark
    auto start = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
    for (int i = 0; i < 50; i++) kernel_xmx(d_C, d_A, d_B, M, N, K, q);
    q.wait();
    auto end = std::chrono::high_resolution_clock::now();
    
    // Report
    double ms = std::chrono::duration<double, std::milli>(end - start).count() / 50;
    double tflops = (2.0 * M * N * K) / (ms * 1e-3) / 1e12;
    std::cout << M << "x" << N << "x" << K << ": " << tflops << " TFLOPS (" 
              << (tflops / 320.0 * 100.0) << "% utilization)" << std::endl;
    
    sycl::free(d_A, q); sycl::free(d_B, q); sycl::free(d_C, q);
}
```

## Success Criteria

- [ ] Compiles with zero errors using AOT BMG flags
- [ ] Runs on GPU (verify with `sycl::gpu_selector_v`)
- [ ] Achieves >100 TFLOPS at 4096×4096 matrix size
- [ ] Utilization >30% of 320 TFLOPS theoretical peak
- [ ] Uses XMX instructions (verify with profiling)

## Common Errors & Solutions

| Error | Cause | Solution |
|-------|-------|----------|
| `no member named 'joint_matrix'` | Missing header | Add `#include <sycl/ext/oneapi/matrix/matrix.hpp>` |
| `Unsupported JointMatrix operation` | Wrong device/JIT | Use AOT compilation with `-device bmg` |
| Low performance (<50 TFLOPS) | Missing large GRF | Add `-options -ze-opt-large-register-file` |
| `no matching function` for load/store | Wrong pointer type | Cast to `multi_ptr` with `address_space_cast` |
| Poor occupancy | Wrong work-group size | Use 8×16 (128 threads) |

## Decision Tree

```
Need matrix multiplication?
├── Yes → Use XMX with joint_matrix
│   ├── Data type: FP16 (sycl::half)
│   ├── Tile: 8×16×16
│   ├── Subgroup: 16 (required)
│   └── Work-group: 8×16 tiles
└── No → Check other optimization guides

Performance < 100 TFLOPS?
├── Yes → Check compilation flags
│   ├── AOT for BMG? → Must use `-device bmg`
│   ├── Large GRF? → Must use `-ze-opt-large-register-file`
│   └── Matrix size? → Try 4096×4096
└── No → Optimization successful!
```

